   "author_association" : "MEMBER",
   "body" : "It doesn't seem ideal to have an integer sanitizer enabled, but then disable it for the whole validation.cpp file.\r\n\r\nThere are currently two similar \"violations\" in the file. Fix both and remove the suppression.\r\n\r\nThis should be ok and safe to do because:\r\n\r\n* The mempool's tx count should never exceed int64's max value, so storing and reading it as int64_t should cover all use cases.\r\n* The vin's size should never exceed int's max value, so casting the unsigned size_t to int shouldn't affect the value or sign.",
